				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In my honest opinion, the ONLY thing that complicates free scrolling is the fact that there are only 2 nametables. Once you decide how to handle that (there are 3 options: use 4-screen mirroring; hide the scrolling artifacts using various tricks; concentrate the artifacts in locations less likely to be noticed), it gets really simple.
<br />
<br />I always hide the scrolling artifacts, either by masking the top 16 scanlines or the leftmost and rightmost 8 columns. Once that's decided, you know where the seams will go ("under" the masked area).</div>

