				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Super Mario Bros. uses a 32x13-metatile (two screen) sliding window in RAM for its collision map. Anything with a destructible playfield (collected coins, broken blocks, etc.) will need to use some sort of collision map in RAM, and that's why SMB1 doesn't have backtracking: so that it can expire columns of the collision map.
<br />
<br />Backtracking, destructibility, no PRG RAM: pick two. Or restrict the level geometry slightly and pick <a href="http://pineight.com/mw/?title=President#Backtracking" class="postlink">one and two halves</a>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

