						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">strat wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">With extra prg-ram, I don't see why free scrolling can't be done in vertical mirroring without artifacts (on ntsc)</div><br />I have been able to see glitches at the top and bottom of the screen using several TVs and NTSC consoles. I simply don't believe the common notion that the glitched scanlines are conveniently cropped in NTSC.<br /><br />Also, PRG-RAM shouldn't have anything to do with the actual scrolling, like I said before. PRG-RAM simply makes fetching the tiles easier, but you can still fetch them in many other ways, even directly from ROM.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">UncleSporky wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Essentially, the statement should be "pick two <strong>unless you don't mind a slight headache, and who in NES development would?</strong>"</div>
